Note:
PACKAGE.JSON INTEROP - Node.js Manifest Adapter (Tier 1)

Adapter from package.json (npm manifest) to the Runa-native
PackageManifest. Like cargo_toml_interop, this module is the mapping
policy - it does not parse JSON itself. JSON parsing is performed by
config/config.runa whose load_from_file dispatches by extension.

FIELDS ADAPTED (per the npm package.json schema):
  name              -> manifest_name
  version           -> manifest_version
  description       -> manifest_description
  license           -> manifest_license
  homepage          -> homepage slot
  repository.url    -> manifest_repository (the .url field if .repository is a table)
  author            -> manifest_authors (npm uses singular; adapter wraps in list)
  contributors      -> manifest_authors (appended)
  keywords          -> manifest_keywords
  dependencies      -> manifest_add_dependency (DEP_REGISTRY)
  devDependencies   -> manifest_add_dev_dependency
  peerDependencies  -> manifest_add_dependency with DEP_FLAG_OPTIONAL
  optionalDependencies -> same with DEP_FLAG_OPTIONAL

VERSION CONSTRAINT MAPPING:
  npm uses the same caret/tilde/exact/range grammar as Cargo, so
  constraint_parse handles npm strings directly. The version_constraint
  module is grammar-compatible with both ecosystems.

EXPLICITLY UNSUPPORTED:
  - Bundled dependencies (legacy npm field), engine-strict policies,
    npm scripts: those are handled by the npm CLI, not the package
    metadata substrate.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/version_constraint.runa" as VC
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/dependency_spec.runa" as Dep
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/package_manifest.runa" as PM

Let NPM_ERR_NO_NAME be 1
Let NPM_ERR_NO_VERSION be 2
Let NPM_ERR_BAD_VERSION be 3
Let NPM_ERR_BAD_DEPENDENCY be 4

@Reasoning
Build a PackageManifest from already-extracted name + version-string
scalars. Parallel to cargo_manifest_from_fields.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Parse the version with version_parse, duplicate the name, construct
the manifest via manifest_create.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the version. Space: O(1) plus the manifest.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strict SemVer parsing rejects partial / malformed inputs.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "npm_manifest_from_fields" takes name as Integer, version_text as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If version_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let version be proc version_parse from VC with version_text
    If version is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let m be proc manifest_create from PM with name_copy, version
    If m is equal to 0:
        proc version_destroy_deep from VC with version
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Return m
End Process

@Reasoning
Adapt an npm "dependencies" entry. npm specifiers may carry a registry
prefix (e.g. "npm:foo@^1.0.0") or a tarball URL but the most common
form is a bare SemVer range string. Callers that have detected url or
tarball forms invoke npm_dependency_url or npm_dependency_tarball
instead.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate the name, parse the constraint via constraint_parse, allocate
a DependencySpec and initialize as DEP_REGISTRY with the npm registry.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on malformed constraint string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "npm_dependency_simple" takes name as Integer, constraint_text as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If constraint_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let constraint be proc constraint_parse from VC with constraint_text
    If constraint is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let registry be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with "https://registry.npmjs.org/"
    Let d be proc dep_create from Dep
    If d is equal to 0:
        If registry is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with registry
        End If
        proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with constraint
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc dep_init_registry from Dep with d, name_copy, registry, constraint
    Return d
End Process

@Reasoning
Adapt a git URL dependency specifier (e.g.
"git+https://github.com/user/repo.git#tag").
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate name and url, optional ref. Initialize as DEP_GIT.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
URL validation is the package manager's job.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "npm_dependency_git" takes name as Integer, url as Integer, ref as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let url_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with url
    If url_copy is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ref_copy be 0
    If ref is not equal to 0:
        Set ref_copy to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with ref
    End If
    Let d be proc dep_create from Dep
    If d is equal to 0:
        If ref_copy is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with ref_copy
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with url_copy
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc dep_init_git from Dep with d, name_copy, url_copy, ref_copy
    Return d
End Process

@Reasoning
Mark a dependency as optional (peer / optionalDependencies semantics).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Set DEP_FLAG_OPTIONAL via dep_set_flag.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "npm_mark_optional" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc dep_set_flag from Dep with d, 1
    Return 1
End Process
